    "created_at": "2017-09-01T20:06:06Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-09-01T20:06:06Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The core of this feature is easy to do: the following line just needs to change to `< 240`:\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/blob/3cf9d47b39601cb1daa9053cfee471809057b831/OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/PaletteEffects/GlobalLightingPaletteEffect.cs#L73\r\n\r\nThe problem, as @GraionDilach mentioned, is that this breaks the water shore rendering.  To fix that we need to be able to be able to specify at least two different sets of index ranges for terrain (up to 255) vs everything else (up to 240), which isn't going to be possible without compatibility-breaking changes to `GlobalLightingPaletteEffect`.\r\n\r\nThe \"easy\" (but bogus) option would be to support multiple `GlobalLightingPaletteEffect`s, one for the terrain, and the other for everything else.  This then breaks the Lua API, as well as making the map overrides slightly uglier.\r\n\r\nThe viable approach is to define a new way of defining palette:range pairs on the traitinfo, but this is going to depend on a larger reworking of our palette modifier infrastructure so as to not hurt performance."
